econet-eth: WHNAT force-to-CPU re-inject batching + rx-poll histogram

The WHNAT half-offload (F3) re-injects each force-to-CPU frame into the stack
with its own dev_queue_xmit(). Under load that is one xmit (and one dev_put)
per frame, all to the same handful of vifs. Batch them: chain the per-poll
force-to-CPU skbs by destination netdev (en75_fcpu_batch[], one slot per vif +
one) and issue a single dev_queue_xmit() per distinct dev at the end of the
NAPI poll -- for IFF_NO_QUEUE / non-tap devs the chain is handed off as one
list, dropping the per-frame queue-lock churn. en75_qdma_rx_process_one() now
takes the batch and just queues; the napi poll inits, then flushes it.

Also adds debug-only rx-poll instrumentation alongside the batch:
atomic64 counters for poll count, total/force-to-CPU frames and a power-of-two
histogram of frames-per-poll (rx_poll_hist_*), exposed via module_param_cb
read-only sysfs, with a rx_stats_reset write knob. Pure diagnostics; no
datapath effect beyond the counters.
